  "contentHtml": "<!-- BEGIN COPYRIGHTED TEXT CHUNK --><html><head></head><body><p><a id=\"passage-26\"><b>Punnamasa</b> (Thag 2.26) <span class=\"altID\">{Thag 171-172}</span></a>&nbsp;<a title=\"Go to top of page\" class=\"back\" href=\"#top\">&nbsp;</a></p>\n\n<div class=\"chapter\">\n\n<div class=\"freeverse\">\nShedding five hindrances\nso as to reach the unexcelled rest\n\t   from the yoke,\ntaking the Dhamma as mirror\nfor knowing &amp; seeing myself,\nI reflected on this body —\n\tthe whole thing,\n\tinside &amp; out,\n\tmy own &amp; others'.\nHow vain &amp; empty it looked!\n</div>\n\n</div>\n\n\n\n</body></html>",
  "summary": "Shed the five hindrances, and what's left?",
